HEADWORD: Sub-bass
<hw>Sub"-bass`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The deepest
pedal stop, or the lowest tones of an organ; the fundamental or ground
bass.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>sub-base</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

